load_dcm[source]

load_dcm(path_to_dicom_dir=None, sort_by_slice_location=True)

Loads DICOM data as a numpy array.

Attributes: path_to_dicom_dir (str): Path to folder containing all dicom files for one subject sort_by_slice_location (bool): Whether to return array ordered by slice location

Returns: pixel_array (arr): Array of pixel data

{% endraw %}

Usage

dcm2array takes a path to one DICOM series (patient).

See the example below:

{% raw %} 
data_path = '../data/knee/'
try:
    image_array = load_dcm(path_to_dicom_dir = data_path, sort_by_slice_location=True)
    plt.imshow(image_array[:,:,6])
    plt.show()
except:
    print('could not load array')
{% endraw %}

load_h5[source]

load_h5(path_to_h5_file=None)

Loads h5 files into numpy array.

Attributes: path_to_h5_file (str): Path h5 file for one subject

Returns: h5_file_dict (dict): Dictionary of pixel data

{% endraw %}

Usage example

{% raw %} 
h5_file = load_h5(path_to_h5_file='../data/knee-segmentation/knee_segmentation.h5')

#Plot
plt.figure(figsize=(10,10))

plt.subplot(121)
plt.title('Image')
plt.imshow(h5_file['img'][:,:,30])

plt.subplot(122)
plt.title('Segmentation image')
plt.imshow(h5_file['seg'][:,:,30])

plt.show()
{% endraw %}
